  <script language="javascript">
   const mapped_urls = new Map();
        mapped_urls.set('about', "/support/about-the-rda/");
        mapped_urls.set('apps_api_desc', "/resources/web-services/rda-external-application-api/");
        mapped_urls.set('daas', "/resources/daas/");
        mapped_urls.set('data-citation', "/resources/citations/");
        mapped_urls.set('metrics', "/resources/metrics/");
        mapped_urls.set('services', "/resources/ancillary-services/");
        mapped_urls.set('rda_web_services', "/resources/web-services/");

        window.onload=respondToHashChange;
        function respondToHashChange() {
          var hash = document.location.hash.substr(1);
          if (hash.charAt(0) == '!') {
            hash = hash.substr(1);
          }
          if (hash.length > 0 && document.location.pathname.indexOf("ajax") < 0) {
            var hash0 = hash;
            var hash1 = "";
            var idx = hash0.indexOf("/");
            if (idx > 0) {
              hash0 = hash0.substr(0, idx);
              hash1 = hash0.substr(idx);
            }
            var m_url = mapped_urls.get(hash0);
            if (m_url != undefined) {
              alert("NOTICE: You are using a legacy URL that will not be supported in the future. If this was a bookmark, you should replace it with the new URL, to which you will now be redirected.");
              document.location = m_url + hash1;
            } else {
              document.location = document.location.pathname + "ajax/#" + hash;
            }
          }
        }
  </script>

   <meta content="Dataset" name="DC.type"/>
   <meta content="https://doi.org/10.5065/D6M043C6" name="DC.identifier"/>
   <meta content="National Centers for Environmental Prediction/National Weather Service/NOAA/U.S. Department of Commerce" name="DC.creator"/>
   <meta content="NCEP FNL Operational Model Global Tropospheric Analyses, continuing from July 1999" name="DC.title"/>
   <meta content="2000-04-12" name="DC.date" scheme="DCTERMS.W3CDTF"/>
   <meta content="UCAR/NCAR - Research Data Archive" name="DC.publisher"/>
   <meta content="These NCEP FNL (Final) Operational Global Analysis data are on 1-degree by 1-degree grids prepared operationally every six hours. This product is from the Global Data Assimilation System (GDAS), which continuously collects observational data from the Global Telecommunications System (GTS), and other sources, for many analyses. The FNLs are made with the same model which NCEP uses in the Global Forecast System (GFS), but the FNLs are prepared about an hour or so after the GFS is initialized. The FNLs are delayed so that more observational data can be used. The GFS is run earlier in support of time critical forecast needs, and uses the FNL from the previous 6 hour cycle as part of its initialization.\n\nThe analyses are available on the surface, at 26 mandatory (and other pressure) levels from 1000 millibars to 10 millibars, in the surface boundary layer and at some sigma layers, the tropopause and a few others. Parameters include surface pressure, sea level pressure, geopotential height, temperature, sea surface temperature, soil values, ice cover, relative humidity, u- and v- winds, vertical motion, vorticity and ozone.\n\nThe archive time series is continuously extended to a near-current date. It is not maintained in real-time." name="DC.description"/>
   <meta content="EARTH SCIENCE &gt; ATMOSPHERE &gt; AIR QUALITY &gt; TROPOSPHERIC OZONE" name="DC.subject"/>
   <meta content="EARTH SCIENCE &gt; ATMOSPHERE &gt; ALTITUDE &gt; GEOPOTENTIAL HEIGHT" name="DC.subject"/>

   <meta content="EARTH SCIENCE &gt; ATMOSPHERE &gt; ATMOSPHERIC WATER VAPOR &gt; WATER VAPOR INDICATORS &gt; HUMIDITY" name="DC.subject"/>

   <meta content="EARTH SCIENCE &gt; ATMOSPHERE &gt; ATMOSPHERIC WINDS &gt; WIND DYNAMICS &gt; CONVECTION" name="DC.subject"/>
   <meta content="EARTH SCIENCE &gt; ATMOSPHERE &gt; ATMOSPHERIC WINDS &gt; WIND DYNAMICS &gt; VERTICAL WIND VELOCITY/SPEED" name="DC.subject"/>
   <meta content="EARTH SCIENCE &gt; ATMOSPHERE &gt; ATMOSPHERIC WINDS &gt; WIND DYNAMICS &gt; VORTICITY" name="DC.subject"/>
   <meta content="EARTH SCIENCE &gt; ATMOSPHERE &gt; CLOUDS &gt; CLOUD MICROPHYSICS &gt; CLOUD LIQUID WATER/ICE" name="DC.subject"/>
   <meta content="EARTH SCIENCE &gt; HUMAN DIMENSIONS &gt; ENVIRONMENTAL GOVERNANCE/MANAGEMENT &gt; LAND MANAGEMENT &gt; LAND USE/LAND COVER CLASSIFICATION" name="DC.subject"/>
   <meta content="EARTH SCIENCE &gt; LAND SURFACE &gt; SOILS &gt; SOIL MOISTURE/WATER CONTENT" name="DC.subject"/>
   <meta content="EARTH SCIENCE &gt; LAND SURFACE &gt; SOILS &gt; SOIL TEMPERATURE" name="DC.subject"/>

    "@context": "http://schema.org",
    "@type": "Dataset",
    "@id": "https://doi.org/10.5065/D6M043C6",
    "name": "NCEP FNL Operational Model Global Tropospheric Analyses, continuing from July 1999",
    "description": "These NCEP FNL (Final) Operational Global Analysis data are on 1-degree by 1-degree grids prepared operationally every six hours. This product is from the Global Data Assimilation System (GDAS), which continuously collects observational data from the Global Telecommunications System (GTS), and other sources, for many analyses. The FNLs are made with the same model which NCEP uses in the Global Forecast System (GFS), but the FNLs are prepared about an hour or so after the GFS is initialized. The FNLs are delayed so that more observational data can be used. The GFS is run earlier in support of time critical forecast needs, and uses the FNL from the previous 6 hour cycle as part of its initialization.\n\nThe analyses are available on the surface, at 26 mandatory (and other pressure) levels from 1000 millibars to 10 millibars, in the surface boundary layer and at some sigma layers, the tropopause and a few others. Parameters include surface pressure, sea level pressure, geopotential height, temperature, sea surface temperature, soil values, ice cover, relative humidity, u- and v- winds, vertical motion, vorticity and ozone.\n\nThe archive time series is continuously extended to a near-current date. It is not maintained in real-time.",

   <script type="text/javascript">
    function setActiveTab(i) {
          var li_list = document.getElementById('datasetTab').getElementsByTagName('li');
          for (n = 0; n < li_list.length; ++n) {
            var a_list = li_list[n].getElementsByTagName('a');
            if (a_list.length > 0) {
              var a = a_list[0];
              if (a.id == i) {
                a.classList.add('active');
                a.ariaSelected = true;
              } else {
                a.classList.remove('active');
                a.ariaSelected = false;
              }
            }
          }
        }

        function setTab() {
          path = document.location.pathname.substr(document.location.pathname.indexOf("/datasets") + 10);
          path = path.substr(path.indexOf("/") + 1)
          qs = document.location.search;
          if (path.length == 0) {
            setActiveTab("description-tab");
          } else if (path.indexOf("dataaccess") == 0 || qs.indexOf("content=dataaccess") >= 0 || path.indexOf("listopt") == 0) {
            setActiveTab("data-access-tab");
          } else if (path.indexOf("citation") == 0) {
            setActiveTab("citation-tab");
          } else if (path.indexOf("documentation") == 0) {
            setActiveTab("documentation-tab");
          } else if (path.indexOf("software") == 0) {
            setActiveTab("software-tab");
          } else if (path.indexOf("metrics") == 0) {
            setActiveTab("metrics-tab");
          }
        }

        function replace_ds_content(response) {
          $('#ds_content').html(response);
          $('html, body').animate({
            scrollTop: $('#ds_content').offset().top - $('header').height()
          });
        }

        function get_ajax_with_history(u, t = '', h = true) {
          $.get(u, replace_ds_content);
          if (h) {
            document.title = "NCAR RDA Dataset d083002 " + t;
            window.history.pushState({'url': u, 'title': t}, "", u);
          }
        }

        window.onpopstate = function(e) {
          setTab();
          if (document.location.hash !== "") return; //Do nothing if tag anchor
          if (e.state) {
            get_ajax_with_history(e.state.url, e.state.title, false);
          } else {
            get_ajax_with_history('', '', false);
          }
        };
   </script>

    function switch_to_metrics() {
            window.history.pushState("","",'metrics')
            $.get('/datasets/d083002/metrics/', replace_ds_content).done(function()
                {
            // Load needs to be synchronous
    	    $.getScript("/static/js/d3.v5.min.0589331f8f4b.js").done(function()
                    {
    	            $.getScript("/static/js/metrics.5742ebee4ac1.js").done(function()
                        {
                        $.getScript("/static/js/add_graph.b8f3faabb1f4.js").done(function()
                            {
                            add_graph('d083002')
                            })
                        });
                    });
                });
             }

  <script type="text/javascript">
   function popModalWindow(w, h) {
  document.getElementById('modal-window-content').innerHTML = '<center><span class="modal-loader"></span></center>';
  mw = document.getElementById('modal-window');
  mc = document.getElementById('modal-window-close');
  if (w) {
    mw.style.width = '75%';
    if (h) {
      mw.style.height = '60%';
    }
  }
  mw_width = parseFloat(mw.offsetWidth) / document.body.offsetWidth;
  mw.style.left = (1. - mw_width) / 2. * 100. + '%';
  mc_width = parseFloat(mc.offsetWidth) / document.body.offsetWidth;
  border_width = parseFloat(mw.style.borderWidth) / document.body.offsetWidth;
  mc.style.left = parseFloat(mw.style.left) + (mw_width * 100.) - (mc_width / 2. * 100.) + - (border_width / 2. * 100.) + '%';
  win_height = window.innerHeight
      ? window.innerHeight
      : document.body.clientHeight;
  mw.style.top = (win_height - parseInt(mw.offsetHeight)) / 2 + 'px';
  mc.style.top = parseInt(mw.style.top) - (mc.offsetHeight / 2) + (parseInt(mw.style.borderWidth) / 2) + 'px';
  document.getElementById('shader').classList.replace('invisible', 'visible');
  mw.classList.replace('invisible', 'visible');
  mc.classList.replace('invisible', 'visible');
}

function hideModalWindow() {
  document.getElementById('modal-window').classList.replace('visible', 'invisible');
  document.getElementById('modal-window-close').classList.replace('visible', 'invisible');
  document.getElementById('shader').classList.replace('visible', 'invisible');
}

function popModalWindowWithGetUrl(w, h, u) {
  popModalWindow(w, h);
  getAjaxContent('GET', null, u, 'modal-window-content');
}

function popModalWindowWithPostUrl(w, h, u, p) {
  popModalWindow(w, h);
  getAjaxContent('POST', p, u, 'modal-window-content');
}

function popModalWindowWithHTML(w, h, html) {
  popModalWindow(w, h);
  document.getElementById('modal-window-content').innerHTML = html;
}
  </script>
  <link href="/css/modal.css" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css"/>
  <div class="invisible" id="modal-window" style="width: 600px; height: 300px; padding: 10px; border: 15px solid #1a658f">
   <div id="modal-window-wrapper">
    <div id="modal-window-content">
     <center>
      <img id="modal-loader"/>
      <div id="modal-loader-text">
      </div>
     </center>
    </div>
   </div>
  </div>
  <div class="invisible" id="modal-window-close" onclick="hideModalWindow()" style="width: 30px; height: 30px">
  </div>
  <div class="invisible" id="shader">
  </div>
